title: Function references missing from __unwind_info on OS X

labels.name: A-runtime
labels.description: Area: std's runtime and "pre-main" init for handling backtraces, unwinds, stack overflows

body:
I tried this code: ```rust fn main() {} ``` In the `__TEXT,__unwind_info` section of the resulting binary, I expected to find an entry for every single routine. Instead, of the 368 routines in the binary, only 217 (~59%) have entries in the `__TEXT,__unwind_info` section. There does not appear to be any obvious determinant for which routines have entries and which do not. Since `_Unwind_FindEnclosingFunction` ultimately uses this info to locate the enclosing routine, these omissions unsurprisingly result in that function (sometimes) returning erroneous results. See, for example, [this unsatisfactory workaround](https://github.com/rust-lang/backtrace-rs/blob/c3c297add8621f66cd4f5032ebfcf13fa69b2468/src/backtrace/libunwind.rs#L68-L80) in backtrace-rs. I believe that the `__TEXT,__unwind_info` section is generated by the linker's [compact_unwind](https://opensource.apple.com/source/ld64/ld64-530/src/ld/passes/compact_unwind.cpp) pass, from records that it finds in the `__LD,__compact_unwind` section. I haven't (yet) determined whether the latter is correctly populated (and therefore whether this is a linker bug) or not (and therefore a compiler bug), although I have tested and observed similar behaviour in clang so am leaning toward the former. ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.47.0-nightly (d6953df14 2020-07-25) binary: rustc commit-hash: d6953df14657f5932270ad2b33bccafe6f39fad4 commit-date: 2020-07-25 host: x86_64-apple-darwin release: 1.47.0-nightly LLVM version: 10.0 ```
